32 Boko Haram terrorists on Sunday willingly surrendered to the Nigerian Army troops at different locations ‎in Borno state. Among them was one Mallam Ibrahim Lawal who surrendered and also handed over one AK 47 rifle with two magazines containing 59 rounds of 7.62mm (special) ammunition. In a statement signed by the Director ‎of Army Public Relations, Brigadier General Texas Chukwu, he added that the surrendered terrorists are currently undergoing interrogation and will be handed over to the appropriate authority on completion.